        <num>CC 2897</num>
        <heading>2897.  Loss caused by fortuitous event</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2897.  Loss caused by fortuitous event
When the thing lent is damaged by a fortuitous event from which the borrower could have protected the thing lent by using a thing of his own or, when being unable to preserve both things, the borrower chose to preserve a thing of his own, he is liable for the damage to the thing lent.</p>
        </content>
